on. More than ever, The Illustrated History of Canada is a must-have reference guide for all Canadians interested in the history - and the future - of our country. Contributors include Ramsay Cook (emeritus, York University), Christopher Moore (Toronto writer), Desmond Morton (McGill University), Arthur Ray (emeritus, University of British Columbia), Peter Waite (emeritus, Dalhousie University), and Graeme Wynn (University of British Columbia).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh1 aCook, Ramsay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorton, Desmond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRay, Arthur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaite, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWynn, Graeme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358788540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773587885423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773587885/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles